<!-- WARNING: this file was generated by Pulumi Docs Generator. -->
<!-- Do not edit by hand unless you're certain you know what you are doing! -->

`mongodbatlas.CloudProviderAccess` allows you to get a single role for a provider access role setup, currently only AWS is supported.

> **NOTE:** Groups and projects are synonymous terms. You may find `groupId` in the official documentation.


{{% examples %}}

## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}





{{< example csharp >}}

```csharp
using Pulumi;
using Mongodbatlas = Pulumi.Mongodbatlas;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var testRole = new Mongodbatlas.CloudProviderAccessSetup("testRole", new Mongodbatlas.CloudProviderAccessSetupArgs
        {
            ProjectId = "<PROJECT-ID>",
            ProviderName = "AWS",
        });
        var singleSetup = Output.Tuple(testRole.ProjectId, testRole.ProviderName, testRole.RoleId).Apply(values =>
        {
            var projectId = values.Item1;
            var providerName = values.Item2;
            var roleId = values.Item3;
            return Mongodbatlas.GetCloudProviderAccessSetup.InvokeAsync(new Mongodbatlas.GetCloudProviderAccessSetupArgs
            {
                ProjectId = projectId,
                ProviderName = providerName,
                RoleId = roleId,
            });
        });
    }

}
```
